.TH man 1 "28 Nov 2019" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple shell made in C to interact with a linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
./hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple_Shell is an sh-compatible command language interpreter that executes
commands read from the standard input.

.SH Return Value

Always 0 for success, other number means failure.

.SH PATH

It will look inside al directions in PATH env variable for executable.

.SH EXECUTE

Compile this shell with the following flags:

	gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh

and then execute the shell with ./hsh

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options will be typed after the main command followed by a space and a
 '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLES

[command] [options]
$ ls -l

total 2696
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu    1486 Nov 27 14:50 engine.c
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu     729 Nov 27 14:50 execute.c
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu     945 Nov 27 14:50 gas.c
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu     814 Nov 27 14:58 holberton.h
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu 2722032 Nov 27 15:13 holberton.h.gch
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu     803 Nov 27 15:15 man_1_simple_shell
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu    1205 Nov 27 15:13 prompt.c
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu    3046 Nov 27 14:50 README.md
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu     215 Nov 27 15:00 shell.c
-rw-rw-r-- 1 ubuntu ubuntu    1434 Nov 27 14:50 string.c

$|

The lines above mean the ls -l command was executed in the long list format
and then the prompt gets printed again thanks to the fork function.

.SH SEE ALSO
.I peerlearning(2), projectbased(2), fullstack(2), Betty(1)

.SH BUGS
Single space required after argument.

